// Notification Service
// Manages browser Notification API permission requests and shows browser notifications
// when Claude is waiting for user input (blocking UI renders).

FUNCTION requestNotificationPermission() -> Promise<NotificationPermission>  EXPORT
  IF the Notification API is unavailable, return 'denied'.
  IF permission is already 'granted' or 'denied', return the current status.
  ELSE request permission from the user and return the result.
  On any error, return 'denied'.

---

FUNCTION showUserInputNotification(uiId) -> Notification | undefined    EXPORT
  IF the Notification API is unavailable, return undefined.
  IF permission is not 'granted', return undefined.
  Create a browser notification titled "Claude is asking..." with body "Click here to respond".
  Use tag = claude-input-<uiId> to prevent duplicate notifications for the same message.
  Set requireInteraction = true so the notification stays visible until the user acts.
  Return the Notification instance, or undefined on error.
